<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Check the following code:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>// Default timezone set to GMT -4 - America/Santiago
date_default_timezone_set('America/Santiago');

$zendDate = new Zend_Date('16/09/2011', Zend_Date::DATE_MEDIUM, 'es_ES');
$zendDate-&gt;setTimezone('UTC');

echo $zendDate-&gt;get(Zend_Date::ISO_8601);</code></pre>

<p>The returned value is 2011-09-16T05:00:00+00:00 while i expect to receive 2011-09-16T04:00:00+00:00. For some reason Zend_Date is adding an extra hour in this case.</p>

<p>I tested with other timezones like America/Sao_Paulo and it worked fine. Although i can't discard that with other timezones it may also fail.</p>

